// Fastest way to convert string to integer in PHP\n$string = "123";\n$integer = (int)$string;\n\n// Explanation:\n// In PHP, the fastest way to convert a string to an integer is by using a cast, as shown above.\n// This method is the fastest because it does not involve any function calls, which can be slow in PHP.\n// Instead, the cast is handled directly by the PHP engine, making it very efficient.\n\n// What happens if it gets unexpected input?\n// If the input string is not a valid integer, the cast will return 0.\n// For example:\n$string = "hello";\n$integer = (int)$string;\n// $integer will be 0\n\n// If the input is an array, the cast will throw a notice and return 0.\n// For example:\n$array = array("hello");\n$integer = (int)$array;\n// $integer will be 0, and a notice will be thrown: "Notice: Array to string conversion"